# Constructor — environment template.
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. NEVER commit a real key.

# CONSTRUCTOR_PII_KEY — AES-256-GCM key encrypting buyer_identity PII columns
# (name/phone/email — Article IV). Accepted encodings of the 32 raw bytes:
#   base64 (exactly 44 chars incl. padding)  or  hex (exactly 64 chars).
# Generate one:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
# Fail-secure by design: any PII operation CRASHES if this is missing or
# malformed — there is deliberately no default key. Note: right-to-erasure
# (eraseIdentity) works WITHOUT the key, so key loss never blocks GDPR erasure.
CONSTRUCTOR_PII_KEY=

# B0a — office-LAN access (RULING 2026-07-14b). Both OPTIONAL:
# leave both unset for loopback-only dev, exactly as before.
#
# CONSTRUCTOR_HOST — bind hostname. Default 127.0.0.1 (loopback only, fail-safe).
# Set to the Mac's office-Wi-Fi IP (e.g. 192.168.1.x) or 0.0.0.0 to let the
# team's phones reach the app on the LAN.
# CONSTRUCTOR_PIN — team PIN, 4-12 digits. When set, every data request needs a
# session minted by entering the PIN once per device (POST /login).
# Fail-secure by design: a non-loopback CONSTRUCTOR_HOST WITHOUT a PIN — or a
# malformed PIN — CRASHES at startup. The PIN never appears in logs or errors.
CONSTRUCTOR_HOST=
CONSTRUCTOR_PIN=
